<h2>Estimated world population by continents, 1800 - 1950</h2>

<img src="wpop01.png" alt="World population by continents 1800-1950"
width="595" height="295" hspace="3" vspace="3" 
style="border: solid medium #CCCCCC; padding: 3 px">
<p>Estimated world population in millions by continents, 1800 - 1950. 
<strong><em>Source:</em></strong>  R. Cameron, <cite>Concise Economic History of the World</cite> 
(New York: O.U.P., 1993)  p.&nbsp;193. 
<a href="#table-format">See below for table format</a>.
Graph produced by StarOffice Calc.</p>
<hr>

<h3>Points to note:</h3>
<ol>
<li>Russia is listed separately because although it is a European
power, it also includes much Asian territory.</li>
<li>The population of Europe is very large for such a small
area. Until recently it has been larger than the population
of Africa.</li>
<li>Throughout the time period shown, more than half of the
world's population has lived in Asia.</li>
</ol>
<hr>
